ating%20whether%20Boeing%20completed%20the%20inspections%20and%20whether%20company%20employees%20may%20have%20falsified%20aircraft%20records%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20agency%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Boeing%20is%20reinspecting%20all%20787%20airplanes%20still%20within%20the%20production%20system%20and%20must%20also%20create%20a%20plan%20to%20address%20the%20in-service%20fleet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20surfaced%20after%20a%20Boeing%20employee%20observed%20an%20%26quot%3Birregularity%26quot%3B%20and%20raised%20the%20issue%20with%20a%20supervisor%20who%20elevated%20it%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20quickly%20reviewed%20the%20matter%20and%20learned%20that%20several%20people%20had%20been%20violating%20company%20policies%20by%20not%20performing%20a%20required%20test%2C%20but%20recording%20the%20work%20as%20having%20been%20completed%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20Stocker%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Boeing%20787%20program%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20promptly%20informed%20our%20regulator%20about%20what%20we%20learned%20and%20are%20taking%20swift%20and%20serious%20corrective%20action%20with%20multiple%20teammates%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stocker%2C%20adding%20that%20engineering%20staff%20determined%20that%20the%20issues%20does%20not%20pose%20an%20immediate%20safety%20of%20flight%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20probe%20adds%20to%20the%20litany%20of%20issues%20facing%20Boeing%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20a%20near-catastrophic%20Alaska%20Airlines%20flight%20in%20January%20in%20which%20a%20panel%20on%20the%20fuselage%20blew%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20has%20given%20the%20company%20three%20months%20to%20present%20a%20plan%20to%20address%20%26quot%3Bsystemic%20quality-control%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoeing's%20management%20of%20the%20787%20came%20under%20question%20at%20an%20April%2017%20Senate%20hearing%20at%20which%20a%20company%20whistleblower%20testified%20that%20he%